        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold mb-10 tracking-tight border-b border-zinc-800 pb-4">Deploying Rift to GitHub Pages</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">GitHub Pages is a free static hosting service for open source projects and documentation. It serves your static site directly from a GitHub repository branch.</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Steps</h3>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-300 mb-6">
            <li>Build your Rift site: <code>npm run build</code></li>
            <li>Push the contents of <code>dist/</code> to a <code>gh-pages</code> branch (or <code>docs/</code> folder for user/organization sites).</li>
            <li>In your repository settings, set GitHub Pages to use the <code>gh-pages</code> branch (or <code>docs/</code> folder).</li>
            <li>Visit your site at <code>https://&lt;username&gt;.github.io/&lt;repo&gt;/</code></li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 mb-6">
            <li>Ensure <code>404.html</code> is present at the root of <code>dist/</code> for error handling.</li>
            <li>Use a tool like <code>gh-pages</code> npm package for easy deployment.</li>
        </ul>
